My experience at the location in Long Beach was terrible. I‚Äôll provide details and I have the paper trail.
I arrived at 4:45pm on a Saturday hoping the store would be open until 6pm for a quick change of spark plugs since A code indicating the #2 cyclometer was not firing. I was traveling and leaving the next day at noon. The store was closing and I was told by an employee to come back at 8am Sunday.

I came back at 7:45am the next day. The store was not open and there were no employees in sight. I waited 20 minutes and still no one. I finally saw a hand written sign on copy paper indicating the store would open at 9:00am. I came back 45 minutes later.

I asked the manager if he could do a tuneup right away and change six spark plugs. His response was that They had to diagnose and ‚Äúsee what else may need attention‚Äù. I knew the Jeep needed a tune up and with one cylinder kicking out a code-keep it simple and see if misfiring and code for away.

I said go ahead and take a look, but please get the spark plugs ordered now so there is no delay. 30 minutes passed before the car was pulled into a bay. Another 30 minutes passed and the manager flagged me over to tell me that the Jeep needed a tune up, a fuel injection servicing and magically it also needed a serpentine belt.   Has anyone ever seen the Dateline and 60 Minutes Type shows that expose the dirty little secrets of fraudulent repairs and false statements that mechanical shops give?

This was textbook Fraud.  the state of California should investigate and send in the cars that have been thoroughly inspected and where there is one clear problem that any experienced mechanic would find, report, repair and move on.

Apparently Discount Tire and this manager are still liking to instill fear and do ‚Äúsell jobs‚Äù on the public‚Äîit‚Äôs disgusting.

Because I was 3 hours from home and trying to get on the road, I was presented an estimate that blew me away‚Äînearly $500 for a tune up, fuel injection service and serpentine belt.

I asked the manager how long it would take to be completely done and to have me driving away. His response was ‚ÄúI can have the belt and plugs here in Under 10 minutes and the car will be ready 45 minutes to an hour. it‚Äôs easy work‚Äù...

I signed the inflated estimate because I needed to get going and did not want to risk a serpentine belt failing, even though I Never heard A frayed belt slapping the underneath of the hood and from what I saw, the belt did not look worn or failing, but the old fear factor the mechanics use takes over.

Fast forward 30 minutes. Still no parts. But guess what? There is an auto zone two blocks away. I offered to go buy the plugs and belt and be back in ten minutes or less and the manager said the parts would be there any minute. More lies.

I said forget it! Get my car out of the stall. I told the manager he was not only providing fraudulent claims of failing parts) but he is making time promises he knows cannot meet so that customers are stuck with a car in the rack.

The new belt was unnecessary and will be returned-as an ethical mechanic that was charging my AC system with Freon confirmed the belt was not work at all and he could read all the white lettering of Part numbers and Brand all over the belt.

<Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
Decent selection of mostly brand new cars (life hack: don't rent anything you wouldn't own yourself, e.g. Nissan, GM, Dodge-Chrysler-Jeep etc.). The employees are professional and friendly. Rates are decent, but if you have AAA, have them make a reservation for you; you might get a pretty good discount.
If your auto insurance doesn't have full coverage, the $16 (minimum) for the bumper-to-bumper coverage is worth it.< /review>

< Text>
They're nice (they are salespeople after all). I had an issue with my custom car audio I took to 3 shops to get professionally fixed for a couple years. In total I spent just over $800+. I went to their store and paid for diagnosis and some part they thought would help. It always work fine when you're listening in their garage but I was fuming angry when I got home I decided the only way I would ever get this fixed is if I did it myself. I got home, took the subs out, and one wire was loose in the butt connector. I took it off, put new wire. and twisted the ends together and wrapped it in electrical tape I haven't had a problem since. I spent $800+ trying to get "pros" to fix something that I diagnosed myself almost instantly and it cost me nothing to fix since I still had leftover wire from when it was installed the initially.</Text>

<review>First, we should have started our journey at an actual Mattress store. I mean, I read and read and read about sleep; sleep positions, average vs light vs heavy sleepers, height weight ratios, snoring, relief of pain in across pressure points, the purple company, the ghost Mattress, the foam kind, the gel kind, the hybrid kind (yeah, that just means foam and coils/aka springs in the same Mattress. Win/win).

Anyway, I now know why the beds in a box offer a 100 or 101 or 102 night in home guarantee. Do you? Well....it's because you can't try them in most stores. Is that always bad? No. You may hit a home run. I'm not saying any product is bad. Truth is, it's not. Things like mattresses suit some of the people some of the time. Let me tell you, I was in the proverbial weeds when it came time to actually choose. The last thing I wanted was to buy one in a box and get less sleep.

I'm totally thankful to have an opportunity to choose my very own Mattress. Honestly, I'm thankful to not have to sleep on the floor. The reality is that sleep is different for everyone and - like shoes - you should get properly fitted. You're over there saying, "no way, lady, are you saying these people can fit me for a matress?" Why, yes, yes, that's exactly it.

Practically every couple has a similar sleep story. Someone is too hot and the other cold. Someone rolls into the other. Someone sleeps on their side comfortable and the other has pain all night complaining the Mattress is too firm/soft/hot or whatever.

It is absolutely worth your time to get measured using the beautiful technology or sleep position and body scanner. I just totally made that sound extra biometric and it's really not. Completely not invasive, not weird, and a carefully executed process. You just get a throw-away coverlet and lie down on a bed to watch about 7 minutes of a video and follow the instructions. Boom! Done!

Also, no more FOMO (fear of missing out). You are now equipped with the best info about sleep regarding yourself and or your sleep partner and you can quickly try mattresses in your particular category for the best fit. Viola! How easy is that?

A Mattress is an investment, no doubt. It doesn't have to break the bank and there are many options from which to choose. The staff is excellent and will guide you every step of the way.

On a final note, do yourself a favor and get fit tested for a pillow. It may sound cheesy but spinal alignment has a lot to do with pain or lack there of. A pillow can make a real difference in how you sleep and ultimately rest.

Shout out to Sit and Sleep Oxnard for guiding us and answering all the questions all while being so friendly and accommodating to our family.

We're happy with our purchase.<//review>< resp>

<Text>I love my new bed!!  I went with the Posturepedic Pro-Adapt hybrid and it is fantastic!  Sales experience was good, delivery was good (very fast and tidy).  Just a word of caution:  they are very serious about the 30 day waiting period to exchange anything.  I had wanted the low profile box spring but followed the suggestion for the regular height.  They provided a measuring tape, and it didn't seem like a couple of inches taller than my old bed would be a problem.  But once it was all assembled those couple of inches actually did make a big difference.  Unfortunately the exchange policy means it will be 30 days before I can change it out for a more appropriate height.  The good news is that it shouldn't be a problem to change after the waiting period.
I would definitely recommend this store for your next mattress purchase!</Text><resp>None<//resp>< GmapID>

< Review>
Like all "specialty" places, this one sells things for more than they could be found somewhere else, but I found it was worth it when the alternative wound up not delivering the adjustable base I'd ordered (after it was reported as being in their delivery hub for over a week). I went in Saturday to buy, it was delivered Sunday before noon. They even took it upstairs and set it up, verifying everything worked as needed, at no extra charge.
While the delivery people were efficient, I wouldn't call them friendly or professional. They made it very clear they didn't like carrying it upstairs, and they weren't interested in answering any questions. They also made it clear they didn't want me to watch - tough, I watched anyway. So minus one star for delivery, but great on everything else.</Review>
